# Aembit Demo: Lambda → Microsoft Graph

This demo shows how Aembit securely brokers credentials from an AWS Lambda function to Microsoft Graph, eliminating the need for secrets in your code.

## Architecture

```
┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐
│  AWS Lambda     │────▶│  Aembit Platform    │────▶│  Microsoft Graph │
│  (Client)       │     │  (Credential Broker)│     │  (Server)        │
└─────────────────┘     └─────────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘
```

1. Lambda executes with IAM role `{{demo_prefix}}-lambda-role`
2. Aembit validates the IAM role identity
3. Aembit requests a token from Azure Entra using WIF
4. Aembit Lambda Layer injects the token into outbound requests
5. Lambda calls Microsoft Graph `/users` endpoint

## Prerequisites

- [Terraform](https://terraform.io) >= 1.0
- AWS CLI configured with appropriate permissions
- Azure CLI configured (`az login`)
- Aembit tenant with API access configured

